Syntax / Grammar Sample Language

1) Variables:

<vType> <name>;						//Simple Variable declaration.*
<vType> <name> = <value>;			//Simple Variable declaration and initiation.
global <vType> <name> = <value>;	//Global Variable declaration and initiation.

Anotations:
* Check if and how it is possible in OCaml.

1.1) List of Basic vType:

int     //Integer
double  //Double
char    //Character
string  //String

1.2) List of Other vType:

1.2.1) Tables:

tbl[<vType>] <name> = new tbl(<int>);												//Simple table declaration and initiation with auto-defind keys.*
tbl[<vType>,<vType>] <name> = new tbl(<int>);										//Simple table declaration and initiation with self-defind keys.
tbl[<vType>] <name> = [<value>, <value>, ...]										//Simple table declaration and initiation through direct input with auto-defind keys.
tbl[<vTypeA>,<vTypeB>] <name> = [<valueA> : <valueB>, <valueA> : <valueB> , ...]	//Simple table declaration and initiation through direct input with self-defind keys.
tbl[<tbl>] <name> = [<tbl>, <tbl>, ...]												//Nested table declaration and initiation through direct input with auto-defind keys.
tbl[<vType>,<tbl>] <name> = [<vType> : <tbl>, <vType> : <tbl>, ...]					//Nested table declaration and initiation through direct input with self-defind keys.

Anotations:
* See wether this is what you meant in the key thing with the table on your whats app message.

2) Mathematical Operations:

2.1) Addition:
<int> + <int> 		//Simple addition for integers.
<double> + <double> //Simple addition for doubles.
<string> + <string> //Simple addition for strings.

2.2) Subtraction:
<int> - <int> 		//Simple subtraction for integers.
<double> - <double> //Simple subtraction for doubles.

2.3) Multiplication:
<int> * <int> 		//Simple multiplication for integers.
<double> * <double> //Simple multiplication for doubles.

2.4) Division:
<int> / <int> 		//Simple division for integers.
<double> / <double> //Simple division for doubles.

2.4.1) Remainder:
<int> % <int> 		//Simple remainder for integers.